A young child has tragically died after a horrific accident where a four-wheel-drive struck him while he was riding his bicycle at a Sydney intersection.

The boy sustained serious head injuries on Monday at 5.45pm and was taken to The Children's Hospital at Westmead where he later died a short time later. 

He was riding his bike at the intersection of Paddock and Capertree streets at The Ponds - north-west of Sydney.

